cff-version: 1.2.0
type: software
message: "If you use this repository, please cite the associated FRACMAT paper and this software archive."
title: "FRACMAT: A vectorized MATLAB framework for continuum damage mechanics with crack band regularization"
authors:
  - family-names: Mavani
    given-names: Jaykumar
  - family-names: Pathirage
    given-names: Madura
repository-code: "https://github.com/Jaykumar9033/FRACMATH"
date-released: "2026-05-31"
version: "1.0.0"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - fracture mechanics
  - continuum damage mechanics
  - crack band regularization
  - finite element method
  - MATLAB
  - Abaqus
  - UMAT
abstract: >-
  FRACMAT is a MATLAB framework for finite element simulation of fracture in
  quasibrittle materials using scalar isotropic continuum damage mechanics,
  modified von Mises equivalent strain, exponential softening, and
  direction-dependent Oliver crack-band regularization.
